/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:272:**No ε-absorption in the main iteration.** Unlike CKN (which uses Young's inequality with free ε to absorb gradient error terms from cutoffs), Vasseur's De Giorgi iteration uses **no free parameters in the core Proposition 3**. Every estimate is done with fixed universal constants. The only source of lossiness is:
