/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:288:**Vasseur avoids this ε-absorption entirely** for the level-set energy estimates, replacing it with the De Giorgi mechanism (Lemma 12 + superlinear recursion). However, the pressure localization still requires Calderón-Zygmund estimates with **fixed L^q constants** (not optimal, but existential), which is where the 4/3 exponent arises.
